Clear-Host  # Clears the console window for better readability.

Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "*Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
Sort-Object | Format-Table Name,Version,InstallDate -AutoSize

Hey Dusty –

Good news, you can close this case. Here’s what learned.


  1.  Contrary to documentation, the host should have been “M365X41559705.SHAREPOINT.COM” versus “M365X41559705.ONMICROSOFT.COM”. This might have been the sole cause of the issue.

  2.  The version of NEA I was running was Netwrix Enterprise Auditor V11.6, version 11.6.0.72 which I had installed on May 10th, 2024. I downloaded and installed the latest version of all the NIC as well.

  3.  The documentation indicates a new browser window will open, looks like 3 windows opened but one was completely blank.

  4.  Despite this, the collection job folder shows error icons on three of the jobs. One because it can’t find an INI file because of on premise remnants being used for the SharePoint online process. Two others because of WARNINGS which show as errors.

Thanks for your assistance on this issue as the tip to use the instant jobs which do setup for solutions was extremely helpful.


Thanks in advance,

bill

Hey Dusty –

 

Good news, you can close this case. Here’s what learned.

 


	Contrary to documentation, the host should have been “M365X41559705.SHAREPOINT.COM” versus “M365X41559705.ONMICROSOFT.COM”. This might have been the sole cause of the issue.
	 
	The version of NEA I was running was Netwrix Enterprise Auditor V11.6, version 11.6.0.72 which I had installed on May 10th, 2024. I downloaded and installed the latest version of all the NIC as well.
	 
	The documentation indicates a new browser window will open, looks like 3 windows opened but one was completely blank.
	 
	Despite this, the collection job folder shows error icons on three of the jobs. One because it can’t find an INI file because of on premise remnants being used for the SharePoint online process. Two others because of WARNINGS which show as errors.
	 


Thanks for your assistance on this issue as the tip to use the instant jobs which do setup for solutions was extremely helpful.


 

 

Thanks in advance,


bill
